<br>
Unfortunately, when it grows beyond just the local community human nature starts to kick in. Without the face and inter-personal contact we tend to forget the reprucussions of our actions. This leads to the breakdown of distribution of goods and services due to corruption, which is exactly why all the &quot;Communist&quot; nations required strong authoritarian governments to survive. history has shown that without a doubt that as human beings we are inherently selfish (I suggest all are, but would not discount someone who said some are not). It is fairly clear to me that there is a very natural explanation for our selfishness if you consider our natural history. I won't go into depth about that as it is a difficult discussion. In any case, with few exceptions, history has shown the selfishness of the human spirit. It has also shown that to be amplified as more people come into power.<br>
<br>
Another problem with such a Communist society is one of self-preservation and protection. With no centralized rule and no governmental structure a communist government would be victimized by stronger nations. Darwin's laws are amplified in struggles for sovreignty. The ability to mobilize for war or conflict would be nearly impossible with a stagnant economy, which is a given in a Communist society. That is, economists have always said that if a pure Socialist/Communist society might be established (despite the hurdles to achiving such) the economy would be stable, but would be stagnant and perpetually poor. Growth would be entirely unlikely due to the numerous economic roadblocks, most notably the incredible hierarchy and beauracracy that would be required to produce and distribute goods. One might say, war is NOT inevitable and that other nations would nto victimize a &quot;peaceful&quot; nation. If history has shown one thing, it is that there will always be those who wish to aquire power and possessins through brute force.<br>
<br>
I would like to think that we as human beings would be capable of such a society and make it work and prosper. Unfortuantely I am a Realist and understand that our very nature prevents this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upalantiri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palantiri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/30/01 5:17:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_bigsmile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Left Wingers</span><hr size=1> Exactly! Communism will never actually work because of human nature. It is an interesting concept, and it works pretty well in Civ2 (was Sid secretly a Communist?) but it would never work outside of a small village setting. <br>
